cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the security challenges in Wireless Body Sensor Networks (WBSN) and proposes a new approach to symmetric cryptographic key establishment based on biometrics physiology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the limitations of WBSN in terms of energy and data-processing, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper focuses on the application of WBSN in the field of health, which could place it in cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of biometrics also suggests that it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) and the focus on the topology of WBSN suggests that it could belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
